title: 254A.16 RESPONSIBILITIES OF THE COMMISSIONER.
text:
[Repealed, 2014 c 262 art 3 s 18]
(a) The commissioner shall provide program and service guidelines and technical assistance to the county boards in carrying out services authorized under section 254A.08.
(b) The commissioner shall recommend to the governor means of improving the efficiency and effectiveness of comprehensive program services in the state and maximizing the use of nongovernmental funds for providing comprehensive programs.
